heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 23.86mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 31.0 hours.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.6mm per hour (ranked 2nd in our records).  The storm lasted 2.6 hours and 6.1mm of precipitation fell during that time.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 7th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of31.0 hours.  It came with 23.86mm of rainfall, at times, falling at 8.3mm per hour.  The lengthiest precipitation event recorded spanned 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025, it was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 24.6mm per hour and a total rainfall of 47.89mm.
